From: Christian Leithner <christian_leithner@comcast.com>
Date: Mon, 20 Jan 2025 21:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add watchdog to build requirements

Pigweed's pw_watch module requires watchdog package, but it's not
currently listed in Matter's build requirements. This causes pw doctor
to fail when trying to load pw_watch.

Adding watchdog to requirements.build.txt ensures it's available in the
venv, and with --system-site-packages enabled, it's also visible to
commands in the native sysroot.

Generated by Copilot AI

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [Yocto-specific]
Signed-off-by: Christian Leithner <christian_leithner@comcast.com>
---
 scripts/setup/requirements.build.txt | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/scripts/setup/requirements.build.txt b/scripts/setup/requirements.build.txt
--- a/scripts/setup/requirements.build.txt
+++ b/scripts/setup/requirements.build.txt
@@ -11,3 +11,5 @@ coloredlogs
 jinja2
 lark
 python-path
+# Required by Pigweed's pw_watch module
+watchdog>=2.1.0
